<paragraph role="heading" id="hd_id4544816" xml-lang="en-US" level="1" l10n="NEW"><variable id="borders"><link href="text/scalc/guide/borders.xhp">User Defined Borders in Cells</link>
</variable></paragraph>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id2320017" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="NEW">You can apply a variety of different lines to selected cells.</paragraph>
<list type="ordered">
<listitem>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id8055665" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="NEW">Select the cell or a block of cells.</paragraph>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id9181188" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="NEW">Choose <item type="menuitem">Format - Cells</item>.</paragraph>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id9947508" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="NEW">In the dialog, click the <emph>Borders</emph> tab.</paragraph>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id7907956" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="NEW">Choose the border options you want to apply and click OK.</paragraph>
</listitem>
</list>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id1342204" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="NEW">The options in the <emph>Line arrangement</emph> area can be used to apply multiple border styles.</paragraph>
<paragraph role="heading" id="hd_id4454481" xml-lang="en-US" level="2" l10n="NEW">Selection of cells</paragraph>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id7251503" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="NEW">Depending on the selection of cells, the area looks different.</paragraph>
<table id="tbl_id4423352">
<tablerow>
<tablecell colspan="" rowspan="">
<paragraph role="tablehead" id="par_id8716696" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="NEW">Selection</paragraph>
</tablecell>
<tablecell colspan="" rowspan="">
<paragraph role="tablehead" id="par_id4677877" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="NEW">Line arrangement area</paragraph>
</tablecell>
</tablerow>
<tablerow>
<tablecell colspan="" rowspan="">
<paragraph role="tablecontent" id="par_id807824" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="NEW">One cell</paragraph>
</tablecell>
<tablecell colspan="" rowspan="">
